body_html:
Thanks Andy.
But we wanted to know which protobuf commit id to be used for Tensorflow.

I could build Protobuf with c59473d53eafadd126502657e5c5c33e952b67ed independently.
Doesn't look like an issue with Protobuf.

I could build TensorFlow master with protobuf commit id ed87c1fe2c6e1633cadb62cf54b2723b2b25c280 successfully.
However, we want to use protobuf commit id c59473d53eafadd126502657e5c5c33e952b67ed or recent one in TensorFlow as fix for 64 bit platform has been committed though c59473d53eafadd126502657e5c5c33e952b67ed. But building TensorFlow gives us an error as mentioned is description.

@poxvoculi @girving Do you have any idea about this?

body:
Thanks Andy.
But we wanted to know which protobuf commit id to be used for Tensorflow.

I could build Protobuf with `c59473d53eafadd126502657e5c5c33e952b67ed` independently. 
Doesn't look like an issue with Protobuf. 

I could build TensorFlow master with  protobuf commit id  `ed87c1fe2c6e1633cadb62cf54b2723b2b25c280` successfully.  
However, we want to use protobuf commit id `c59473d53eafadd126502657e5c5c33e952b67ed` or recent one in TensorFlow  as fix for 64 bit platform has been committed though `c59473d53eafadd126502657e5c5c33e952b67ed`. But building TensorFlow gives us an error as mentioned is description. 

@poxvoculi @girving Do you have any idea about this?
